⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Demographic Transition
node POP · POP · ⟦The Demographic Transition:POP:2e0efb⟧

WHO   — The Demographic Transition — high→low birth & death
WHAT  — The arc of human populations: death rates fall first (a population boom), then birth rates follow, then both settle low.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because the one population we most want to forecast — our own — moves through a patterned, if contested, transition.
HOW   — By a four-stage model (sometimes five), fitting the industrialized West better than everywhere.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I describe how a people goes from many-born-many-die to few-born-few-die. I'm a pattern, not a prophecy — don't mistake me for law.

